race.comment: TAINUI (7) has needed the two runs to bring him to his top and will relish this trip. Went forward and failed to match motors late when a battling sixth over 1200m at Coonamble. Winning rider hops back aboard from the good draw. Goes close. RHYTHM IS A DANCER (1) tough old gelding who was on the quick back-up when a gritty third over 1400m at Dubbo. Nasal strip goes on, and fitness should take him a long way. INVINCIBLE RED (9) wound up strongly but just failed to pick up the winner when second over 1600m at Tamworth. Should be near his peak for this and goes close with the drop in weight. BESTOWER (3) caught the eye first-up when a slashing fourth over 1400m at Warwick Farm behind Winston Hills. Has a sound second-up record and has clearly come back well. Keep safe.
